{"title_page": "Hennie Otto", "text_new": "{{Infobox golfer\n| name              = Hennie Otto\n| image             = Hennie Otto.JPG\n| imagesize         = <!-- e.g. 250px (default is 200px) -->\n| caption           = \n| fullname          = Hendrik Johannes Otto\n| nickname          = Hennie\n| birth_date        = {{Birth date and age|1976|6|25|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Boksburg]], [[South Africa]]\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1976|6|25|df=y}} -->\n| death_place       = \n| height            = {{height|m=1.76|precision=0}}\n| weight            = {{convert|82|kg|lb st|abbr=on}}\n| nationality       = {{ZAF}}\n| residence         = [[Boksburg]], [[South Africa]]\n| spouse            = \n| partner           = \n| children          = \n| college           = \n| yearpro           = 1998\n| retired           = <!-- Year retired -->\n| tour              = [[European Tour]]<br>[[Sunshine Tour]]\n| extour            = <!-- Former tours which a member of -->\n| prowins           = 16\n| pgawins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour wins -->\n| eurowins          = 3\n| japwins           = <!-- Number of Japan Golf Tour wins -->\n| asiawins          = <!-- Number of Asian Tour wins -->\n| sunwins           = 13\n| auswins           = <!-- Number of PGA Tour of Australasia wins -->\n| nwidewins         = <!-- Number of Nationwide Tour wins -->\n| chalwins          = 1\n| champwins         = <!-- Number of Champions Tour wins -->\n| seneurowins       = <!-- Number of European Seniors Tour wins -->\n| otherwins         = <!-- Number of Other wins -->\n| majorwins         = <!-- Number of Major Championship wins -->\n| masters           = DNP\n| usopen            = DNP\n| open              = T10: [[2003 Open Championship|2003]]\n| pga               = CUT: 2008\n| wghofid           = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame member ID -->\n| wghofyear         = <!-- World Golf Hall of Fame year inducted -->\n| award1            = <!-- Achievement or award details -->\n| year1             = <!-- Year(s) of achievement or award -->\n| award2            = \n| year2             = \n| awardssection     = <!-- location of awards page or section -->\n}}\n'''Hendrik Johannes \"Hennie\" Otto''' (born 25 June 1976) is a [[South African people|South African]] [[professional golfer]].\n\nOtto was born in [[Boksburg]]. He has played golf on the [[European Tour]] since 2000 having graduated from the [[Challenge Tour]], but has only finished within the top 100 on the Order of Merit twice, in 2003 when he finished tied for tenth at [[The Open Championship]] on his major championship d\u00e9but and in 2008 when he won the [[Italian Open (golf)|Italian Open]] and finished 37th on the Order of Merit.\n\nOtto has won 13 times on the [[Sunshine Tour]] since 1999. He won his second title on the European Tour (co-sanctioned by the Sunshine Tour) at the [[South African Open (golf)|South African Open Championship]] in November 2011.\n\n==Professional wins (16)==\n===European Tour wins (3)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!! Date!!Tournament!!Winning score!!Margin of<br>victory!!Runner-up\n|-\n|align=center|1\n|align=right|11 May [[2008 European Tour|2008]]\n|[[Italian Open (golf)|Methorios Capital Italian Open]]\n|\u221225 (65-66-63-69=263)\n|1 stroke\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Oliver Wilson]]\n|-\n|align=center|2\n|align=right|27 Nov [[2011 European Tour|2011]]\n|[[SA Open Championship]]<sup>1</sup>\n|\u221214 (70-67-65-72=274)\n|1 stroke\n|{{flagicon|AUT}} [[Bernd Wiesberger]]\n|-\n|align=center|3\n|align=right|31 Aug [[2014 European Tour|2014]]\n|[[Italian Open (golf)|Open d'Italia]] <small>(2)</small>\n|\u221220 (67-62-71-68=268)\n|2 strokes\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[David Howell (golfer)|David Howell]]\n|}\n<sup>1</sup>Co-sanctioned by the [[Sunshine Tour]]\n\n'''European Tour playoff record (0\u20131)'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!No.!!Year!!Tournament!!Opponent!!Result\n|-style=\"background:#F2C1D1;\"