{"title_page": "PNKP", "text_new": "{{Infobox_gene}}\n'''Bifunctional polynucleotide phosphatase/kinase''' is an [[enzyme]] that in humans is encoded by the ''PNKP'' [[gene]].<ref name=\"pmid10446192\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Jilani A, Ramotar D, Slack C, Ong C, Yang XM, Scherer SW, Lasko DD | title = Molecular cloning of the human gene, PNKP, encoding a polynucleotide kinase 3'-phosphatase and evidence for its role in repair of DNA strand breaks caused by oxidative damage | journal = J. Biol. Chem. | volume = 274 | issue = 34 | pages = 24176\u201386  | date = September 1999 | pmid = 10446192 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1074/jbc.274.34.24176 }}</ref><ref name=\"pmid10446193\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Karimi-Busheri F, Daly G, Robins P, Canas B, Pappin DJ, Sgouros J, Miller GG, Fakhrai H, Davis EM, Le Beau MM, Weinfeld M | title = Molecular characterization of a human DNA kinase | journal = J. Biol. Chem. | volume = 274 | issue = 34 | pages = 24187\u201394  | date = September 1999 | pmid = 10446193 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1074/jbc.274.34.24187 }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: PNKP polynucleotide kinase 3'-phosphatase| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=11284| accessdate = }}</ref>\n\n== Interactions ==\n\nPNKP has been shown to [[Protein-protein interaction|interact]] with [[DNA polymerase beta]]<ref name=pmid11163244>{{cite journal | vauthors = Whitehouse CJ, Taylor RM, Thistlethwaite A, Zhang H, Karimi-Busheri F, Lasko DD, Weinfeld M, Caldecott KW | title = XRCC1 stimulates human polynucleotide kinase activity at damaged DNA termini and accelerates DNA single-strand break repair | journal = Cell | volume = 104 | issue = 1 | pages = 107\u201317  | date = January 2001 | pmid = 11163244 | doi = 10.1016/S0092-8674(01)00195-7 }}</ref> and [[XRCC1]].<ref name=pmid11163244/><ref name=pmid17353931>{{cite journal | vauthors = Ewing RM, Chu P, Elisma F, Li H, Taylor P, Climie S, McBroom-Cerajewski L, Robinson MD, O'Connor L, Li M, Taylor R, Dharsee M, Ho Y, Heilbut A, Moore L, Zhang S, Ornatsky O, Bukhman YV, Ethier M, Sheng Y, Vasilescu J, Abu-Farha M, Lambert JP, Duewel HS, Stewart II, Kuehl B, Hogue K, Colwill K, Gladwish K, Muskat B, Kinach R, Adams SL, Moran MF, Morin GB, Topaloglou T, Figeys D | title = Large-scale mapping of human protein-protein interactions by mass spectrometry | journal = Mol. Syst. Biol. | volume = 3 | issue = 1 | pages = 89 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17353931 | pmc = 1847948 | doi = 10.1038/msb4100134 }}</ref>\n\n== Clinical Implications ==\n\nThe human gene encoding PNKP has been observed to be mutated in patients.\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin | 2}}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Whitehouse CJ, Taylor RM, Thistlethwaite A, Zhang H, Karimi-Busheri F, Lasko DD, Weinfeld M, Caldecott KW | title = XRCC1 stimulates human polynucleotide kinase activity at damaged DNA termini and accelerates DNA single-strand break repair | journal = Cell | volume = 104 | issue = 1 | pages = 107\u201317 | year = 2001 | pmid = 11163244 | doi = 10.1016/S0092-8674(01)00195-7 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Chappell C, Hanakahi LA, Karimi-Busheri F, Weinfeld M, West SC | title = Involvement of human polynucleotide kinase in double-strand break repair by non-homologous end joining | journal = EMBO J. | volume = 21 | issue = 11 | pages = 2827\u201332 | year = 2002 | pmid = 12032095 | pmc = 126026 | doi = 10.1093/emboj/21.11.2827 }}\n* {{cite journal | vauthors = Strausberg RL, Feingold EA, Grouse LH, Derge JG, Klausner RD, Collins FS, Wagner L, Shenmen CM, Schuler GD, Altschul SF, Zeeberg B, Buetow KH, Schaefer CF, Bhat NK, Hopkins RF, Jordan H, Moore T, Max SI, Wang J, Hsieh F, Diatchenko L, Marusina K, Farmer AA, Rubin GM, Hong L, Stapleton M, Soares MB, Bonaldo MF, Casavant TL, Scheetz TE, Brownstein MJ, Usdin TB, Toshiyuki S, Carninci P, Prange C, Raha SS, Loquellano NA, Peters GJ, Abramson RD, Mullahy SJ, Bosak SA, Mc