{"title_page": "Candy Ken", "text_new": "'''Jakob Kasimir Hellrigl''', known as '''Candy Ken''', is an Austrian [[rapper]], [[model (person)|model]], [[TikToker]], and [[artist]]. He started his career as a rapper in 2014. He combines a masculine appearance with feminine pop culture.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://melmagazine.com/candy-ken-does-l-a-8601682b8630#.4ig3kasg6|title=Candy Ken Does L.A.|last=Stone|first=Zak|date=2016-08-19|newspaper=MEL Magazine|access-date=2016-11-29}}</ref>He has become famous for his TikTok videos where he shows his wealth and lifestyle throughout the videos that he creates.\n\n== Early life and education  ==\nBorn in [[Bregenz]], Austria, Hellrigl studied photography and film design at the [[Lette-Verein]] college in Berlin, but dropped out of his studies in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.friday-magazine.ch/de/2015/03/19/gestatten-das-ist-candy-ken.html|title=Gestatten: Das ist Candy Ken|newspaper=[[20 Minuten|20 Minuten Friday]]|author=Anina Frischknecht|date=March 19, 2015|access-date=2016-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161129082921/http://www.friday-magazine.ch/de/2015/03/19/gestatten-das-ist-candy-ken.html#|archive-date=2016-11-29|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHe attended [[Wenatchee High School]] at [[Wenatchee, Washington]] for a year where he played football. During his high school years, he met his two best female friends, whose whereabouts are unknown, Isabella and Payton, who he has said inspired him to pursue his music career. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.papermag.com/is-a-jacked-berlin-based-rapper-named-candy-ken-fashions-new-it-boy-1427518366.html|title=Is a Jacked Berlin-Based Rapper Named Candy Ken Fashion's New It Boy?|magazine=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]|author=Nadja Sayej|date=February 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\nWhile studying at college, he invented the [[gender-bending]] persona of Candy Ken,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://fuckingyoung.es/sugar-pop-interview-with-candy-ken/|title=Sugar Pop - Interview with Candy Ken!|date=April 15, 2015|magazine=Fucking Young!|author=Luca Imbimbo|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-11-22}}</ref> incorporating imagery from [[Hello Kitty]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.out.com/popnography/2015/2/27/who-hell-candy-ken|title=Who the Hell Is Candy Ken?|work=[[Out (magazine)|Out]]|author=''Out'' editors|date=February 27, 2015|access-date=2016-11-22}}</ref> Japanese [[Kawaii]] culture,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.de/style/69608-fashion-s-favorite-candy-ken|title=Fashion's Favorite: Candy Ken|website=[[MTV Germany]]|language=de-DE|access-date=2016-11-19}}</ref> [[Barbie]] dolls<ref name=\"NewNowNext\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.newnownext.com/hello-kitty-gets-nasty-with-model-rapper-candy-ken/03/2016/|title=Hello Kitty Gets Nasty With Model-Rapper Candy Ken|website=[[NewNowNext]]|author=Cody Gohl|date=March 28, 2016}}</ref> and pink clothing in his dress style and visual appearance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://galoremag.com/rapper-candy-ken-on-how-to-stop-being-basic/|title=Breaking Down Stereotypes With Hello Kitty Lover Candy Ken|date=2015-08-03|newspaper=Galore|language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.papermag.com/candy-ken-sorry-not-sorry-1610369288.html|title=Premiere: Candy Ken Preaches Self-Love In \"Sorry Not Sorry\"|last=papermagazine|date=2016-02-18|newspaper=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]|access-date=2016-11-22}}</ref>\n\n''Welcome to Candy Land'' in 2014 as a self-directed video series on [[YouTube]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://noisey.vice.com/alps/article/welcome-to-candyland-video-175|title=\"Welcome To Candyland\" ist das Seltsamste und Beste, das wir diese Woche gesehen haben|website=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|language=de|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161127222217/https://noisey.vice.com/alps/article/welcome-to-candyland-video-175|archive-date=2016-11-27|url-status=dead}}</ref> The music is produced by Lets Go Radio, and distributed by [[Spinnup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kaltblut-magazine.com/candy-ken-welcome-to-candyland-part-i-ii/|title=Candy Ken - Welcome To Candyland Part I + II|work=Kaltbut|date=November 23, 2014|access-date=2016-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161125174420/http://www.kaltblut-magazine.com/candy-ken-welcome-to-candyland-part-i-ii/|archive-date=November 25, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe video series was re-made as a short film ''Welcome to Candy Land'', which won an award at the Austrian short film festival Alpinale in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://alpinale.at/events/welcome-to-candyland/|title=Welcome to Candyland|newspaper=ALPINALE|access-date=2016-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161130185533/http://alpinale.at/events/welcome-to-candyland/#|archive-date=2016-11-30|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015 he released the second EP ''Candy Ken Paradise'' produced by DJ Smokera and distributed by Spinnup.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/candy-ken-paradise-ep/1275408114|title=Candy Ken Paradise - EP by Smokera & Candy Ken|work=[[Apple Music]], [[iTunes]] (US)|date=September 2, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2015 he released a third EP, ''Daddy 69'', containing five songs and five videos. Four videos are directed by him, and the video for the song \"69\" is directed by London-based underground director Kassandra Powell.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hungertv.com/feature/candy-ken-visits-a-vhs-sex-dungeon-for-the-video-for-69/|title=Candy Ken visits a VHS sex dungeon for the video for \"69\"|newspaper=[[Rankin (photographer)|Hunger TV]]|language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-22}}</ref> Candy Ken appeared on  [[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]  in April 2018 on a segment of Guess Who's High <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7mMj2wiiDXY.</ref>\n\nIn June 2016 he released his first album ''Real Talk'' containing twelve songs, ten of which were made in collaboration with the rapper Gigi Tays.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kaltblut-magazine.com/candy-kens-debut-album-realtalk-is-on-the-way/|title=CANDY KEN`S Debut Album #REALTALK Is On The Way|website=Kalbult|author=Marcel Schlutt|date=May 6, 2016|access-date=2016-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161129083354/http://www.kaltblut-magazine.com/candy-kens-debut-album-realtalk-is-on-the-way/|archive-date=November 29, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The release of the album was promoted with a club party at Visions Video Bar in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://autre.love/interviewsmain/2016/5/16/one-night-in-candy-land-an-interview-with-the-larger-than-life-candy-ken|title=One Night In Candy Land: An Interview With The Larger Than Life Candy Ken|newspaper=Autre Magazine|access-date=2016-11-29}}</ref> The album was also produced by Smokera and the video for the song \"What I Like\" directed by Powell.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kaltblut-magazine.com/video-world-premiere-candy-ken-feat-gigi-tays-what-i-like-na-na-na/|title=Video World Premiere: Candy Ken feat. Gigi Tays - WHAT I LIKE (Na Na Na)|work=Kaltblut|date=September 6, 2016|access-date=November 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161126001440/http://www.kaltblut-magazine.com/video-world-premiere-candy-ken-feat-gigi-tays-what-i-like-na-na-na/|archive-date=November 26, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>  He mentions the American rapper [[Riff Raff (rapper)|Riff Raff]] as his main musical and artistic influence for the album.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.maccosmetics.com/culture/global-heroes/candy-ken|title=Culture - Global Heroes - Candy Ken|newspaper=MAC Cosmetics - Official Site|access-date=2016-11-02}}</ref>\n\n===Modeling===\nHis modeling career started when he was noticed on [[Instagram]] in 2015 by stylist and [[Diesel (brand)|Diesel]] brand creative designer [[Nicola Formichetti]], who invited him to do a [[photo shoot]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.papermag.com/chilling-with-berlin-modelpartyboy-candy-ken-1427623322.html?slide=dBfZWR|title=Chilling With Berlin Model/Partyboy, Candy Ken|last=PAPERMAG|date=2015-07-30|newspaper=PAPERMAG|access-date=2016-11-22}}</ref> for a photo session in Formichetti's Japanese magazine ''FREE''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://freemagazine.jp/candy-ken/|title=CANDY KEN {{!}} \u30a6\u30a3\u30e1\u30f3\u30ba\uff06\u30e1\u30f3\u30ba\u30d5\u30a1\u30c3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u8a8c\u300eFREE MAGAZINE\u300f|website=freemagazine.jp|access-date=2016-11-17}}</ref> Formichetti introduced him to the photographer [[Terry Richardson]], who also made a photo shoot with him in full frontal nudity for the magazine ''[[Man About Town (magazine)|Man about Town]]''. At the same time he was booked as a fashion model by the Italian Diesel clothing brand at the Pride Week in [[New York City]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kaltblut-magazine.com/candy-ken-gets-naked-for-terry-richardsondson/|title=Candy Ken gets naked for Terry Richardson {{!}} KALTBLUT Magazine|website=www.kaltblut-magazine.com|access-date=2016-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113183843/http://www.kaltblut-magazine.com/candy-ken-gets-naked-for-terry-richardsondson/|archive-date=2016-11-13|url-status=dead}}</ref>  He also made a [[Runway (fashion)|runway]] appearance at the opening for designer Roberto Piqueras' fashion show at Berlin's alternative fashion week,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vogue.com.tw/vogue_talk/insider/kowei/detail-693.html|title=Be Yourself! Interview with Candy Ken - kowei \u63d2\u756b\u8a66\u8863\u9593 - kowei \u2223 \u98a8\u683c\u9054\u4eba \u2223 VOGUE\u6642\u5c1a\u7db2|website=www.vogue.com.tw|access-date=2016-11-22}}</ref> and for Japanese fashion designer [[Michiko Koshino]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.cision.com/may/r/iconic-designer-michiko-koshino-celebrates-the-30th-anniversary-of-her-prolific-brand--michiko-londo,c2119226|title=Iconic designer Michiko Koshino celebrates the 30th anniversary of her prolific brand, Michiko London|website=News Powered by Cision|access-date=2016-11-29}}</ref> He has been in photo shoot sessions for ''[[VMAN]]'' magazine,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.auraphotoagency.com/eng/n/vman-magazine-featurin-candy-ken_392.html|title=VMAN MAGAZINE featurin' CANDY KEN, Aura Photo Agency|website=www.auraphotoagency.com|access-date=2016-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161126001558/http://www.auraphotoagency.com/eng/n/vman-magazine-featurin-candy-ken_392.html|archive-date=2016-11-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Paper (magazine)|''Paper'']] magazine, [[Vogue (magazine)|''Vogue'']] Taiwan,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vogue.com.tw/vogue_talk/insider/kowei/detail-694.html|title=\u505a\u81ea\u5df1\uff01\u7c89\u7d05\u7cfb\u6f6e\u7537 Candy Ken \u53f0\u7063\u9996\u8a2a - kowei \u63d2\u756b\u8a66\u8863\u9593 - kowei \u2223 \u98a8\u683c\u9054\u4eba \u2223 VOGUE\u6642\u5c1a\u7db2|website=www.vogue.com.tw|access-date=2016-11-22}}</ref> and the Korean edition of ''[[Dazed]]'' magazine<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kr.dazeddigital.com/2016/02/27/candy-ken/|title=CANDY KEN|last=Dazed|date=2016-02-27|website=dazedkorea|access-date=2016-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161129144724/http://kr.dazeddigital.com/2016/02/27/candy-ken/|archive-date=2016-11-29|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n===Studio albums===\n*''Real Talk'' (2016)\n*''Flamingo'' (2018)\n\n===EPs===\n*''Welcome to Candy Land'' (2015)\n*''Basic Bitches'' (2015)\n*''Candy Ken Paradise'' (2015)\n*''Daddy69'' (2015)\n*''Candy Trap'' (2017)\n*''Send Nudes'' (2017)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Candy Ken}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Bregenz]]\n[[Category:Austrian rappers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "'''Jakob Kasimir Hellrigl''', known as '''Candy Ken''', is an Austrian [[rapper]], [[model (person)|model]], [[TikToker]], and [[artist]]. He started his career as a rapper in 2014. He combines a masculine appearance with feminine pop culture.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://melmagazine.com/candy-ken-does-l-